Auth
    controller
        AuthController ---> Controller for login/register
    dto
        LoginRequest ---> Entity with the login information
        LoginResponse ---> Login response
        RegisterRequest ---> Entity with the sing-up information
    security
        JwtService ---> Create JWT token
    service
        AuthService ---> Service to register and Login

Common
config
    SecurityConfig ---> Create a bean for the password encode and security for who can access to the endpoints

user
    entity
        User ---> Entity for User on the DB, JPA and Hibernate administrate the representation from a user on the DB
        Role ---> Mange the role for each user
    repository
        UserRepository ---> JPA repository with the basic crud to mange the db and let us create new queries

application.yaml
    ---> Information about db and hibernate

WorkFlow - Sing-up
Controller /register (AuthController)
-> Call Service register function using the right dto (LoginRequest)(AuthService)
-> register call the repository to valida if the user is already register(UserRepository), if no;
    create new user(User)
    assign a role(role)
    hashing the password using SecurityConfig and PasswordEncoder
    save(UserRepository)

WorkFlow - Login
Controller /login (AuthController)
-> Call Service login function using the right dto (RegisterRequest)(AuthService)
-> register call the repository to validate if the user and password(validate using PasswordEncoder) match, if yes;
    generate a token (JwtService)
    return token





